page.text: November 11 was the day on which the armistice ending World War I was signed;
this day has been set aside to commemorate the men and women of the United
States who have honorably served our nation in the armed forces; and
on Veteran s Day 20 1 4 we offer our support to those veterans who suffer illnesses
and disabilities resulting from their service; and
there are approximately four thousand veterans living in the Town of Chelmsford;
NOW, THEREFORE, we, the Chelmsford Board of Selectmen, do hereby recognize Tuesday ,
November 11, 20 1 4 as Veteran s Day and on this day urge the residents of
Chelmsford to remember the personal contributions of all veterans in their
community and nation and to demonstrate their respect and gratitude in appropriate
Signed this eleventh day of November, 2014
